The course primarily provides practical knowledge of how to prepare procurement contracts and documents related to public procurement. The course is conducted by experts in their field who have been dealing with procurement documents at a high level.Objectives/eesmärkid:  This course provides in-depth and practical knowledge of how to prepare procurement documents related to public procurement. Previous documents are also analyzed and the written language of procurement documents is practiced. The knowledge gained during the course has been valued on the labor market.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Professional knowledge and skills. After successfully passing the course, the student can: -	orient in the public procurement refister and public documents -	thoroughly knows the objectives, processes and conditions of organizing public procurement -	prepare independently detailed procurement documents -	analyse previously prepared procurement documents -	use written language corresponding to official documents and read procurement-related laws -	find and notice typical mistakes made in procurement documents -	use the programs needed to make and format documents (e.g. MS Word, MS Excel) Transferable competencies. Upon successful completion of the course, the student can: -	write a legal text and use formal written language -	use the digital tools and e-environments needed for work -	work in a group and lead it -	formulate the needs of the organization/company and analyze them -	define specific procurement goals -	reflect and evaluate his/her learning experience and the usability of the practical skills; -	write and choose specific document and format depending on the need;
